The Goal-Question-Metric approach [10] has been  used for the derivation of metrics based on quality criteria. The  goals, measurement questions and the corresponding metric are  explained in the following sub-sections. The quality goals are  derived from standards like ISO 25010 [13] and ISO 26262 [14].  Only a few quality goals and corresponding metrics for software  architecture which can be measured statically are explained. A  measurement question can have multiple metrics associated with  it. The whole range of metrics for each quality characteristic and  measurement question are not covered within the scope of this  paper. Table 1 shows the metrics applied to validate some of the  product line goals. The metrics are explained in detail in the  following sub-sections.
